    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"cccv blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0bcaa5bc-159f-5b7f-aa05-7cfe4f9ffd92","excerpt":"At some point, simple “Cmd + Tab” is not fast and precise enough to switch between applications. Using “Cmd + Space” to search for application is ok, but too…","html":"<p>At some point, simple “Cmd + Tab” is not fast and precise enough to switch between applications. Using “Cmd + Space” to search for application is ok, but too slow for frequently used applications.</p>\n<p>Let’s setup a few custom shortcuts like <code class=\"language-text\">caps+E</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">caps+S</code> switch between your most used applications like <strong>VS code</strong>, <strong>Slack</strong> and <strong>Chrome</strong> (on macOS)!</p>\n<h2 id=\"1-karabiner-elements---key-combination-mapping\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1-karabiner-elements---key-combination-mapping\" aria-label=\"1 karabiner elements   key combination mapping permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Karabiner-Elements - key combination mapping</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://karabiner-elements.pqrs.org\">Karabiner</a> is a popular keyboard customier for macOS. We’re going to use it to change the key <code class=\"language-text\">caps</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">shift+cmd+option+ctrl</code> (“hyper key”), because we</p>\n<ul>\n<li>don’t want to use too-simple shortcuts that might have been used by other applications already</li>\n<li>don’t want to press the 4 keys at once</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Follow the <a href=\"https://karabiner-elements.pqrs.org/docs/getting-started/installation/\">instructions from the official website</a> to install application, and don’t miss all the security config changes required.</p>\n<p>After Karabiner is properly set up, go to <a href=\"https://ke-complex-modifications.pqrs.org/#Jesse_Tutorial_Hyper_Plus_Others\">https://ke-complex-modifications.pqrs.org/#Jesse_Tutorial_Hyper_Plus_Others</a> to import this <code class=\"language-text\">CAPS_LOCK to Hyper/Escape</code> rule set. Actually only the <code class=\"language-text\">CAPS_LOCK to HYPER (SHIFT+COMMAND+OPTION+CONTROL) or ESCAPE (If Alone)</code> rule is needed. (btw I’ve been long used to have <code class=\"language-text\">Caps</code> replaced with <code class=\"language-text\">Esc</code>).</p>\n<p>I only keep this rule after import.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/864db9b5714cbb3a2ae2583cb66900df/49853/karabiner-mapping.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.39240506329114%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"karabiner-rule\"\n        title=\"karabiner-rule\"\n        src=\"/static/864db9b5714cbb3a2ae2583cb66900df/f058b/karabiner-mapping.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/864db9b5714cbb3a2ae2583cb66900df/c26ae/karabiner-mapping.png 158w,\n/static/864db9b5714cbb3a2ae2583cb66900df/6bdcf/karabiner-mapping.png 315w,\n/static/864db9b5714cbb3a2ae2583cb66900df/f058b/karabiner-mapping.png 630w,\n/static/864db9b5714cbb3a2ae2583cb66900df/40601/karabiner-mapping.png 945w,\n/static/864db9b5714cbb3a2ae2583cb66900df/78612/karabiner-mapping.png 1260w,\n/static/864db9b5714cbb3a2ae2583cb66900df/49853/karabiner-mapping.png 2224w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"2-hammerspoon---define-the-action-of-shortcut\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-hammerspoon---define-the-action-of-shortcut\" aria-label=\"2 hammerspoon   define the action of shortcut permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. Hammerspoon - define the action of shortcut</h2>\n<p>Now we need <a href=\"https://www.hammerspoon.org/\">Hammerspoon</a> to define what will be executed after pressing our hyper key shortcuts. <a href=\"https://www.hammerspoon.org/\">Follow the instruction</a> and go to github release page to download and install it.</p>\n<p>The final step is to create your <code class=\"language-text\">~/.hammerspoon/init.lua</code>. It doesn’t matter if you don’t know how to write Lua yet. Here is my <code class=\"language-text\">init.lua</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"lua\"><pre class=\"language-lua\"><code class=\"language-lua\">hyperKey <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token string\">'shift'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'control'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'option'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'command'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">-- reload config</span>\nhs<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>hotkey<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">bind</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>hyperKey<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"r\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  hs<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">reload</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">end</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\nappShortcutMap <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  b <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Google Chrome'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  e <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Visual Studio Code'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  s <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Slack'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  t <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'iTerm'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> k<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> v <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span> <span class=\"token function\">pairs</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>appShortcutMap<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">do</span>\n  hs<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>hotkey<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">bind</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>hyperKey<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> k<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    hs<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>application<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">launchOrFocus</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>v<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- if hs.application.get(v):isFrontmost() then</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">--   hs.application.get(v):hide()</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- else</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">--   hs.application.launchOrFocus(v)</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- end</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">end</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">end</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>I’ve set up a few <code class=\"language-text\">Caps+?</code> shortcuts for my frequently used applications. You can change the mapping as you like.</p>\n<p>After updating the script, you have to reload it.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/adba03b4a698460a826f7855bdd5f370/669eb/hammerspoon-console.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 93.0379746835443%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"hammerspoon-console\"\n        title=\"hammerspoon-console\"\n        src=\"/static/adba03b4a698460a826f7855bdd5f370/f058b/hammerspoon-console.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/adba03b4a698460a826f7855bdd5f370/c26ae/hammerspoon-console.png 158w,\n/static/adba03b4a698460a826f7855bdd5f370/6bdcf/hammerspoon-console.png 315w,\n/static/adba03b4a698460a826f7855bdd5f370/f058b/hammerspoon-console.png 630w,\n/static/adba03b4a698460a826f7855bdd5f370/40601/hammerspoon-console.png 945w,\n/static/adba03b4a698460a826f7855bdd5f370/669eb/hammerspoon-console.png 1244w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>If you have alrady ran the script, and are going to further modify it, the <code class=\"language-text\">Caps+R</code> shortcut should have registered to reload the config of Hammerspoon. You can use it instead of going to the console and click “Reload config”.</p>\n<h2 id=\"3-profit\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#3-profit\" aria-label=\"3 profit permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>3. Profit</h2>\n<p>It takes some time to suppress the urge to press <code class=\"language-text\">Cmd+Tab</code>, and use the new shortcuts. But once you get used it, it’s much faster to switch between applications.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Switching applications with keyboard shortcut on macOS","date":"October 02, 2021","description":null}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2021-09-29-amazing-sqlite/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Amazing SQLite"}},"next":null},"pageContext":{"id":"0bcaa5bc-159f-5b7f-aa05-7cfe4f9ffd92","previousPostId":"39b8df88-98a1-539c-9abc-a89d8e1e28ab","nextPostId":null}},
